# CoinTrace — Test Suite

## Structure

```
test/
├── mocks/                      # Shared native mocks (Arduino, LittleFS, FreeRTOS, NVS)
├── mock_impl.cpp               # Mock implementations compiled into every native test
├── test_config_manager/        # ConfigManager unit tests (24 cases)
├── test_fingerprint_cache/     # FingerprintCache unit tests (6 cases)
├── test_log_entry/             # LogEntry formatting unit tests (11 cases)
├── test_logger/                # Logger dispatch + transport unit tests (13 cases)
├── test_measurement_store/     # MeasurementStore validation unit tests (11 cases)
├── test_nvs_manager/           # NVSManager round-trip unit tests (9 cases)
├── test_ring_buffer/           # RingBufferTransport unit tests (16 cases)
└── test_vector_compute/        # VectorCompute unit tests (9 cases — LDC1101 signal math)
```

Total: **108 test cases** across 8 suites. All run on native (PC) — no device required.

## Running Tests

**From terminal (recommended on Windows):**
```powershell
pio test -e native-test
```

**From VS Code:** PlatformIO sidebar → Test → native-test → ▶ Run All Tests

## Windows: VS Code Test Runner `ERRORED`

If running via VS Code Test Explorer produces:
```
Error: *** [test_logger.o] The process cannot access the file because it is
being used by another process
native-test:test_logger [ERRORED]
```

This is a **Windows Defender file lock** on `.pio\build\` object files — not a code bug.
Fix (one-time, requires admin PowerShell):
```powershell
Add-MpPreference -ExclusionPath "D:\GitHub\CoinTrace\.pio"
```

See `docs/guides/DEBUGGING.md` §8 — "Native tests ERRORED" for full details.

## Adding New Tests

1. Create `test/test_<module>/test_<module>.cpp`
2. Add a mock in `test/mocks/` if the module uses Arduino/ESP32 APIs
3. Implement mock stubs in `test/mock_impl.cpp` if needed
4. Run `pio test -e native-test` — PlatformIO auto-discovers the new suite
